,"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Montgomery","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and northern Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Sainte-Foy-de-Montgomery and Saint-Germain-de-Montgomery (Calvados). In Ireland this surname was present in the medieval period, died out, and was then reintroduced from Scotland in the 17th century. It has been Gaelicized in Ireland as <b>Mac Iomaire</b> and in Scotland as <b>Mac Gumaraid</b>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Giles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Much altered English vernacular form of the Late Latin name <i>Aegidius</i>, from Greek <i>Aigidios</i> (a derivative of <i>aigidion</i> ‘kid, young goat’), via Old French <i>Gide</i>. It was the name of an 8th‐century saint who, according to tradition, was an Athenian citizen who fled to Provence because he could not cope with the fame and adulation caused by his power to work miracles, in particular by healing the lame and crippled. This was not a particularly common name in the Middle Ages and its use seems to have been confined to certain families and localities."],"variants":[{"name":"Gyles","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Giles ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Giles de Montgomery was born about 1130, in Scotland, her father, Hugh Montgomery, was 32 and her mother, Elizabeth Gordon, was 27. She married Shaw Mac in Toisich MacDuff 1st Chief of Clan Mackintosh before 1150, in Fife, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1185, at the age of 56."},"et":{"about 1130–1185":"umbes 1130–1185","1130–1185":"1130–1185","1135–Male":"1135–Surnud","1125–1179":"1125–1179","1150–1209":"1150–1209","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","before 1130":"enne 1130","before 1150":"enne 1150","from 1125 to 1179":"from 1125 to 1179","about 1155":"umbes 1155","1209":"1209","about 1130":"umbes 1130","Scotland":"Scotland","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1130–1185":"noin 1130–1185","1130–1185":"1130–1185","1135–Male":"1135–Kuollut","1125–1179":"1125–1179","1150–1209":"1150–1209","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1105–Female":"1105–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","before 1130":"ennen vuotta 1130","before 1150":"ennen vuotta 1150","from 1125 to 1179":"vuodesta 1125 vuoteen 1179","about 1155":"noin 1155","1209":"1209","about 1130":"noin 1130","Scotland":"Scotland","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1130–1185":"environ 1130–1185","1130–1185":"1130–1185","1135–Male":"1135–Décédé","1125–1179":"1125–1179","1150–1209":"1150–1209","1155–Male":"1155–Décédé","1100–Male":"1100–D